Kajo passed away on Monday morning while receiving treatment at Sayidna Fatma Hospital in MombasaKajo, 78, was part of the Feisal FC squad which is the only team from the Coast to have ever won the Kenya Premier League title in 1965His last prayers will be held at TSS mosque before his burial at Tangana Muslim Cemetery in Ganjoni area on Monday afternoon Former Feisal FC and Harambee Stars striker, Ali Kajo has died. 
Kajo passed away on Monday morning while receiving treatment at Sayidna Fatma Hospital in Mombasa.
Kajo, 78, was part of the Feisal FC squad which is the only team from the Coast to have ever won the Kenya Premier League title in 1965.
He is best remembered for scoring the last goal for pre-independence Kenya and netting the first goal for the national team post-independence. 



